  "diagnostic_features": [
    "H-2 appears as most downfield singlet around 9.13 ppm due to position between two nitrogens",
    "H-4 and H-6 are equivalent and appear around 9.15 ppm with small meta coupling (1.2 Hz)",
    "H-5 is most upfield aromatic proton around 7.33 ppm, appears as triplet due to meta coupling",
    "C-2 and C-4/C-6 carbons appear around 157-158 ppm, C-5 is most upfield around 124 ppm",
    "Strong solvent dependence with downfield shifts in protic solvents due to hydrogen bonding to nitrogens",
    "Electron-donating substituents cause large upfield shifts, especially at C-2 position"
  ]
